# ============================================================================
# TEST POLYGON TRIANGULATION - Face Triangulation Test
# ============================================================================
#
# PURPOSE:
#   Tests the SceneManager's automatic triangulation of polygons with more
#   than 3 vertices. OBJ format allows arbitrary polygons; the parser must
#   convert them to triangles for rendering.
#
# TRIANGULATION METHOD:
#   The SceneManager uses FAN TRIANGULATION:
#
#   For polygon with vertices [V0, V1, V2, V3, V4, ...]:
#     Triangle 1: V0, V1, V2
#     Triangle 2: V0, V2, V3
#     Triangle 3: V0, V3, V4
#     ...
#
#   Example for a quad (4 vertices):
#
#       V3 -------- V2
#        |  \    /  |
#        |    V0    |
#        |  /    \  |
#       V0 -------- V1
#
#     Creates: Triangle(V0,V1,V2), Triangle(V0,V2,V3)
#
# LIMITATION:
#   Fan triangulation works correctly ONLY for CONVEX polygons.
#   Concave polygons may produce incorrect results (self-intersecting
#   triangles). This is a known limitation of simple fan triangulation.
#
# TEST CASES:
#
#   1. SQUARE (4 vertices)
#      Vertices: 1-4
#      Face: f 1 2 3 4
#      Expected triangles: 2 (quad split into 2 triangles)
#
#      V3(0,1) ---- V2(1,1)
#         |           |
#         |           |
#      V0(0,0) ---- V1(1,0)
#
#   2. PENTAGON (5 vertices)
#      Vertices: 5-9
#      Face: f 5 6 7 8 9
#      Expected triangles: 3
#
#          V7
#         /   \
#       V8     V6
#        |     |
#       V9 --- V5
#
#   3. HEXAGON (6 vertices)
#      Vertices: 10-15
#      Face: f 10 11 12 13 14 15
#      Expected triangles: 4
#
#        V12 --- V11
#       /           \
#     V13           V10
#       \           /
#        V14 --- V15
#
# TRIANGULATION FORMULA:
#   For an N-vertex polygon:
#   Number of triangles = N - 2
#
#   Total expected: 2 + 3 + 4 = 9 triangles
#
# ============================================================================

mtllib ./quadric_materials.mtl

# Square (4 vertices)
v 0.0 0.0 0.0
v 1.0 0.0 0.0
v 1.0 1.0 0.0
v 0.0 1.0 0.0

# Pentagon (5 vertices)
v 2.0 0.0 0.0
v 2.951 0.309 0.0
v 2.588 1.0 0.0
v 2.0 1.0 0.0
v 1.412 0.691 0.0

# Hexagon (6 vertices)
v 4.0 0.0 0.0
v 4.866 0.5 0.0
v 4.866 1.5 0.0
v 4.0 2.0 0.0
v 3.134 1.5 0.0
v 3.134 0.5 0.0

usemtl diffuse_green

# Square (should produce 2 triangles)
f 1 2 3 4

# Pentagon (should produce 3 triangles)
f 5 6 7 8 9

# Hexagon (should produce 4 triangles)
f 10 11 12 13 14 15

